<task><p>We take logarithms to solve exponential equations.
  <md><mrow>5^x \amp = 125~~~~~~~~\text{Take the log of both sides.}</mrow>
      <mrow>\log_5 {5^x} \amp = \log_5 {125}~~~~~~~\text{Simplify each side.}</mrow>
      <mrow> <fillin/> \amp = <fillin/></mrow></md>

The solution, <m>\log_5 {125} = 3</m>, is the exponent in the original equation. Once again, we see that a logarithm is just an exponent; in this case it is the exponent on base 5 that will give us 125.</p>

<p>You can think of taking a logarithm as a command that says "find me the exponent!"</p></task>

