<activity><title>Solving Base 10 Equations</title>
<introduction><p>We can now solve exponential equations that have base 10.
  <md><mrow>10^x \amp = 150~~~~~~~~~~~~\text{Take the log base 10 of both sides.}</mrow>
      <mrow>\log {10^x} \amp = \log {150}~~~~~~~~~~~~\text{Simplify each side.}</mrow>
      <mrow>x \amp = 2.1761~~~~~~~~~~~~\text{Check:}~10^{2.1761} = 150.003</mrow></md>
  Logarithms are very sensitive to round-off error. You should keep four places of accuracy in your answers.</p></introduction>

